Butter the baking dish, set aside. Preheat the oven to 350Â°. In a large saucepan, bring the milk and 2 cups water to a boil over high heat. Pour in the grits, stirring constantly until moistened. Remove from the heat and stir in the butter, seasonings, cheese and eggs. Pour into the prepared baking dish and bake for 1 hour. Let cool to room temperature and cut into diamond shapes. Pan fry in butter until golden on both sides.